{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6a089c34-5727-4e86-ac07-bd21cff891a2","content":"No workflow files found here, so here's the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### Changes needed:\n\n**1. Register your package on nuget.org for trusted publishing:**\n- Go to nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers\n- Add your GitHub repository, workflow file path, and optionally an environment\n\n**2. Update your workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` passed to `--api-key` | No API key needed |\n| No special permissions | `permissions: id-token: write` |\n| N/A | Package registered for trusted publishing on nuget.org |\n\n**3. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once confirmed working.\n\nThe OIDC token is automatically sent by `dotnet nuget push` when no `--api-key` is provided and the NuGet source supports trusted publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38547b59-aa5d-4fc2-a0ee-077a0b7b19d5","outputTokens":360,"requestId":"A405:203D52:135E820:15CC73F:69F93EEF"},"id":"61b8f003-2481-4ed9-acd1-02b62c0a0b72","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:03.274Z","parentId":"255383f3-53df-413b-8b54-82c83f9b0fe2"}
